{
  "texts": [
    "Especially for agricultural products with complex compositions, different bands with spectral properties beyond the visible range are necessary to characterize completely.",
    "While RGB imaging techniques can be cost-effective, they cannot be used for many applications due to limited spectral information.",
    "To overcome these limitations and utilize the benefits of both RGB and HSI, many research endeavors have focused on hyperspectral image reconstruction from RGB images (Arad et al. 2018 (Arad et al., 2020;; Zhang et al. 2022).",
    "This process utilizes deep learning models to bridge the gap between the simplicity and spatial richness of RGB imaging and the detailed spectral analysis offered by HSI.",
    "By converting RGB images into HSI with advanced deep learning algorithms, it becomes possible to accurately estimate the spectral signatures at a pixel-by-pixel level."
  ]
}